# alias

## Synopsis
`alias [NAME=VALUE | NAME VALUE ...]`

## Description
Create or list command aliases. Without arguments, `alias` prints the currently defined aliases. When invoked with an assignment, the alias is persisted to the NovaCLI configuration file.

## Examples
- `alias` — list all aliases.
- `alias ll='ls -la'` — create a shortcut named `ll`.
- `alias greet echo hello` — alias `greet` to `echo hello`.
